	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>To be honest Gart, I took Izmalis's bait and answered that question with a lame answer when my sentiments actually are closer to yours on it. He attempted to define the debate on terms of the potential child... I think the debate issues are in terms of the possible parents.<br />
<br />
My main issues are really as stated, <br />
<br />
***the Gov should not have the right to force people to undergo medical procedures against their will.<br />
***Sex would be only for procreation<br />
***We have previous evidence of the ramifications of the same decision and the results were not pretty.<br />
<br />
There are other side issues I find, like the fact that the population explosion that we cannot handle as it is right now, would be yet even more uncontrolable, and people would loose the ability to control their lives if they were forced to have children before they were ready, but those are secondary to those above.<br />
<br />
Abortion is a tricky subject. It involves the definition of life and when life should be defined from and noone has an answer to that one... It involves the most Important/catastrophic decision that a person / couple can make .... whether they can accept responsibility for another person or not, and whether they WANT to accept responsibility for another person or not and are willing to accept the risks involved in pregnancy. That decision is never taken lightly, and is a momment that one thinks about every single day afterward, whether they had the child or not.<br />
<br />
I really don't believe it revolves around whether the embryo can become a person that is good or not... that is undecidable. But clearly it depends on how the people involved deem they need to proceed. I don't believe that once something begins to grow inside someone that all rights of that person are sacrificed... and to the man that is involved, that his entire future becomes irrevokably changed by governmental mandate, but I will go more into that belief (opinion) later.</p>
	
	
	
		<div>__________________<br /><img src="http://www.greylake.org/UncleSam.jpg" border="0" alt=""></div>
	
