	<!-- message -->
	<p>yeah the grey is a - being offended is not allowed - zone. So feel free to speak freely. If you have any doubts, look up millmans posts.<br />
<br />
The history of the debate over here is this... for about 100 years after the United States was established, women and midwives were the only authority on childbirth... That meant if a child were to be aborted it was entirely the decision of the woman (perhaps with input from others). Around the late 1800s America was in deeply depressed economic times. During this time, most of the population was now in cities, and no longer providing self sufficiently on farms. So women were making the decision to abort children, since they could not feed them. Church going folk saw that this was happening ALOT, and sometimes even without the fathers consent (remember we were VERY religious and paternal at this time). <br />
<br />
So, many places started to enact laws saying abortion was illegal. Oh they still happened, and it was rarely ever prosecuted... but it was far more dangerous, and the stigma level was huge on a woman, so that many either a) chose to have children they didn't want, b) waited dramatically long to abort the child, and then finally made the decision, which is a mess, and likely for the mother to die c) a variety of options from a and b.  During the women's rights movements of the 1960s here, after blacks had rights, women have voting rights, but not alot of personal rights... we had a Supreme Court that uphold a court case that firmly gave a woman the right to have an abortion... this case was called Roe vs Wade.<br />
<br />
From there it has been a bloody battle between the sides ever since, even going ironically so far as to have anti-abortion activists blowing up abortion clinics (killing everyone inside) "to save lives".  <br />
<br />
Now let's be honest, I am deplicting only one half of this story. Pro choice people would paint a very different picture in different tones, so I want to be clear on that, but that is basically the state of things today.<br />
<br />
There has never been a national referendum on abortion and some would say one is needed. But you see even that process cannot be trusted. You have leaders of the right that do what ever they can to alienate minorities like gays in this country while members of their own families are GAY. i.e. the vice president and his daughter. So honest debate on these issues is not going to happen, at this point you have politicians that will pander to the right so heavily it is hard to imagine a truthful debate.<br />
<br />
Is there any benefit in having these 2 sides debate?  Yes. <br />
<br />
Human life (or as I believe) life in general is a rare thing. It should not be taken for granted, and it should not be taken lightly. The right moderates the left from becomming monsterous in their apathy for social conventions, while the left moderates the right from becomming totalitiarian facists bent on some judao christian mockery lead by fanatics.   <br />
<br />
The key is to compromise.... which has happened even in the abortion debate here. After some period of time, abortions are still illegal.</p>
	
	
	
