	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>Chutoi</b><br /><i>I have a real issue with the religious nuts (aka "pro-life") labels.  According to those sanctimonious bible-thumpers, those horrible baby-murdering abortion-mongers are pro-abortion, not pro-choice.<br />
<br />
I'm not a big fan of abortion.  If it gets that far, 99/100 times someone just plain screwed up (pardon the pun, please!).  The fact is, the mother should be able to decide whether she can support a child, is ready to have a child, can handle a child, etc.<br />
<br />
Perhaps we should rename the "pro-life" totalitariaist religious nut bible-thumpers, "pro-nazi's" as they feel they have a right to dictate how an otherwise free woman must spend 9 months of her life, risk her health (child-birth is NOT 100% safe), change her body (pregnancy has other effects), etc.<br />
<br />
Then they have the audacity to chide us pro-choicers about not discussing when a life becomes a life and whether a few cells in a body constitutes a baby, or whether a disadvantaged life is still better than death.  When we can clone people from a skin scraping, are they going to prosecute simple assaults as murder because those cells could have been a baby?<br />
