	<p>I won't say I'm militantly pro-choice, but I'm close.  Contraceptives fail.  People taking substantial precautions can still get pregnant.  Someone who is planning on a child can have a massive reversal in fortunes--fired, injured, divorced, widowed, separated, etc.  People have sex while drunk or drugged.  Young girls may have sex and not know better because their parents are too chicken-**** to talk to them.  Rape victims . . .<br />
<br />
There are a lot of reasons people may not want to have a child.  Who are we to argue with their reasoning?  I don't like the idea of abortion, but I DO respect their wishes.  Why would we force a woman to have a child and put it into an already stressed and imperfect system that can't cope with the current demands of adoption and foster kids.<br />
<br />
Any pro-nazi talking to be had better already have at least one adopted child before they start spouting their "abortion is murder" crap at me.  <br />
<br />
Telling someone else what to do for 9 months is a form of coercion (as if standing around in front of clinics that allow abortion and screaming at already emotionally fragile women isn't bad enough).  Coercion is done in prisons for law-breakers.  Coercion is done by totalitarianist governments.  Coercion is done by kidnappers, rapists, and all kinds of other unsavory people.<br />
<br />
Last I checked, this was supposed to be the land of the free.  My usual response to the pro-nazi's is just that:  "**** off, you nazi!"<br />
<br />
/grumps<br />
<br />
Chutoi</p>
	
	
	
